{"version": "https://jsonfeed.org/version/1.1", "title": "XM Zheng's Blog", "home_page_url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/", "feed_url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/feed_json_updated.json", "description": null, "icon": null, "authors": [], "language": "en", "items": [{"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/a-fast-method-for-partial-fraction-decomposition/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/a-fast-method-for-partial-fraction-decomposition/", "title": "A fast method for partial fraction decomposition", "content_html": "<h1>A fast method for partial fraction decomposition</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"../assets/covers/a-fast-method-for-partial-fraction-decomposition.png\"></p>\n<p>!!! warning \"Generated by AI\"</p>\n<p>\u8be5\u65b9\u6cd5\u9002\u7528\u4e8e\u53e3\u7b97</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/a-fast-method-for-partial-fraction-decomposition.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2025-11-22T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Math", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/fix-semicolon-parsing-logic-within-comments-in-sicps-sqlite-shell-py/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/fix-semicolon-parsing-logic-within-comments-in-sicps-sqlite-shell-py/", "title": "Fix semicolon parsing logic within comments in SICP's sqlite_shell.py", "content_html": "<h1>Fix semicolon parsing logic within comments in SICP's <code>sqlite_shell.py</code></h1>\n<p>SICP \u7684 <code>sqlite_shell.py</code> \u975e\u5e38\u795e\u5947\u7684\u65e0\u6cd5\u5904\u7406 <code>/* */</code> \u4e2d\u7684 <code>;</code>\uff0c\u4f1a\u4ea7\u751f\u62a5\u9519\uff1a</p>\n<p><code>bash\nsqlite&gt; /*;*/;\nnear \"*\": syntax error</code></p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/fix-semicolon-parsing-logic-within-comments-in-sicps-sqlite-shell-py.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2025-12-28T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["SICP", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/from-hash-tables-to-dictionaries-the-missing-part-of-sicp/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/from-hash-tables-to-dictionaries-the-missing-part-of-sicp/", "title": "From hash tables to dictionaries: the missing part of SICP", "content_html": "<h1>From hash tables to dictionaries: <br> the missing part of SICP</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\u7b14\u8005\u5728\u7814\u8bfb <a href=\"https://github.com/KEDIT2007/NJU-SICP-Essays/blob/main/dict-and-python-oop/Dictionaries%20and%20Python%20OOP.md\">Dictionaries and Python OOP</a> \u7684\u65f6\u5019\u610f\u8bc6\u5230\u81ea\u5df1\u5bf9 Python \u5b57\u5178\u7684\u5b9e\u73b0\u4e86\u89e3\u4e0d\u591f\uff0c\u4fbf\u5728\u8fd9\u4e00\u65b9\u5411\u8fdb\u884c\u4e86\u6df1\u5165\u63a2\u7d22\u3002</p>\n<p>\u6211\u4eec\u7684 <a href=\"https://sicp.pascal-lab.net/2025/\">SICP</a> \u8bfe\u7a0b\u6ca1\u6709\u6d89\u53ca\u8fd9\u4e00\u6570\u636e\u7ed3\u6784\uff0c\u6211\u76f8\u4fe1\u4e5f\u6709\u5176\u4ed6\u5b66\u4e60\u8005\u60f3\u8981\u6df1\u5165\u4e86\u89e3\u5b57\u5178\u7684\u5b9e\u73b0\u539f\u7406\uff1b\u56e0\u6b64\u6211\u4e0d\u59a8\u5199\u4e00\u4efd\u8bb2\u4e49\uff0c\u6765\u7cfb\u7edf\u5730\u8bb2\u89e3 Python \u5b57\u5178\u7684\u8bbe\u8ba1\u601d\u60f3\uff0c\u5e0c\u671b\u540e\u6765\u8005\u4e5f\u80fd\u5c11\u8d70\u4e00\u4e9b\u5f2f\u8def\u3002</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>!!! note\n    \u8fd9\u4efd\u8bb2\u4e49\u4e0d\u9002\u5408\u4ee5\u4e0b\u8bfb\u8005\uff1a</p>\n<pre><code>- \u671f\u671b\u4ee5\u6b64\u5b66\u4e60\u57fa\u672c\u8bed\u6cd5\u3002\n- \u671f\u671b\u4ee5\u6b64\u63d0\u9ad8\u8bfe\u5185\u6210\u7ee9\u3002\n\n\u5efa\u8bae\u5728\u9605\u8bfb\u540e\u5b8c\u6210\u914d\u5957\u7ec3\u4e60\u3002\n</code></pre>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/from-hash-tables-to-dictionaries-the-missing-part-of-sicp.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2026-01-17T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["SICP", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/git-tutorial-for-dlco/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/git-tutorial-for-dlco/", "title": "Git tutorial for DLCO", "content_html": "<h1>Git tutorial for DLCO</h1>\n<p>\u5728\u6b64\u7b80\u8ff0\u5982\u4f55\u5728\u5b9e\u9a8c\u5e73\u53f0\u4e2d\u914d\u7f6e\u7f51\u7edc\u8fde\u63a5\uff0c\u5e76\u4e0e NJU Git \u540c\u6b65\u3002</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/git-tutorial-for-dlco.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2026-04-09T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["DLCO", "Guide"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/how-to-build-a-pastebin-website/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/how-to-build-a-pastebin-website/", "title": "How to build a pastebin website", "content_html": "<h1>How to build a pastebin website</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"../assets/covers/how-to-build-a-pastebin-website.png\"></p>\n<p>\u8fd1\u65e5\u7ed9\u539f\u6765\u7684 Pastebin \u6362\u4e86\u4e00\u4e2a\u670d\u52a1\u5668\uff0c\u91cd\u65b0\u90e8\u7f72\u4e00\u904d\uff0c\u6b63\u597d\u5199\u4e00\u7bc7\u6559\u7a0b\u3002</p>\n<p>\u6211\u9009\u62e9\u7684\u662f <a href=\"https://privatebin.info/\">PrivateBin</a>\u3002</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/how-to-build-a-pastebin-website.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2026-01-06T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/i-set-up-my-homepage/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/i-set-up-my-homepage/", "title": "I set up my homepage!", "content_html": "<h1>I set up my homepage!</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"../assets/covers/i-set-up-my-homepage.png\"></p>\n<p>\u6b63\u597d\u6709\u4e00\u4e2a\u95f2\u7f6e\u7684\u57df\u540d\u4e0d\u77e5\u9053\u62ff\u6765\u5e72\u5565\u597d\uff0c\u6709\u4eba\u5efa\u8bae\u6211\u641e\u4e2a\u4e2a\u4eba\u4e3b\u9875\u3002</p>\n<p>\u6240\u4ee5\u5c31\u6709\u5566\uff0c\u8fd9\u4e2a\u7b80\u964b\u7684\u4e3b\u9875\uff1a</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://zhengximing.com/\">https://zhengximing.com/</a></p>\n<p>\u76ee\u524d\u5565\u90fd\u6ca1\u6709..</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/i-set-up-my-homepage.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2025-12-27T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Living"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/markdown-macros-for-typora/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/markdown-macros-for-typora/", "title": "Markdown macros for Typora", "content_html": "<h1>Markdown macros for Typora</h1>\n<p>\u6ce8\u610f\u62ec\u53f7\u7684 4 \u4e2a\u53ea\u6709 Typora \u80fd\u7528\uff0c\u56e0\u5176\u8f83\u4e3a\u7279\u522b\u7684 MathJax \u914d\u7f6e\u3002</p>\n<p>\u4e0d\u5efa\u8bae\u7528\u8fd9 4 \u4e2a\uff0c\u5982\u679c\u4f60\u4e0d\u53ea\u7528 Typora \u7684\u8bdd\u3002</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/markdown-macros-for-typora.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2025-12-13T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Math", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/organized-notes-of-mit-1801sc/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/organized-notes-of-mit-1801sc/", "title": "Organized notes of MIT 18.01SC", "content_html": "<h1>Organized notes of MIT 18.01SC</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"../assets/covers/organized-notes-of-mit-1801sc.png\"></p>\n<h3>Description:</h3>\n<p>An archive of MIT 18.01SC Single Variable Calcul...</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/organized-notes-of-mit-1801sc.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2025-08-26T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Math", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/some-questions-i-set/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/some-questions-i-set/", "title": "Some questions I set", "content_html": "<h1>Some questions I set</h1>\n<p>\u662f\u4e00\u4e9b\u5f88\u4e71\u7684\u4e00\u4e2a\u6574\u7406\uff0c\u4ece\u5bb6\u91cc\u7ffb\u51fa\u6765\u7684\u4e00\u5806\u4e1c\u897f\u3002\u6ca1\u4ec0\u4e48\u7528\u3002</p>\n<p>\u53ea\u662f\u89c9\u5f97\u5f03\u4e4b\u53ef\u60dc\u3002</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/some-questions-i-set.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2026-01-17T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/something-about-vivado-and-verilog/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/something-about-vivado-and-verilog/", "title": "Something about Vivado and Verilog", "content_html": "<h1>Something about Vivado and Verilog</h1>\n<p>!!! info\n    \u8bfe\u7a0b\u540d\u79f0\uff1a\u6570\u5b57\u903b\u8f91\u4e0e\u8ba1\u7b97\u673a\u7ec4\u6210\u5b9e\u9a8c</p>\n<pre><code>\u5f00\u53d1\u677f\uff1aNexys A7-100T\n\n\u9879\u76ee\u4ed3\u5e93\uff1a&lt;https://github.com/simonzxm/dlco-exp&gt;\n</code></pre>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/something-about-vivado-and-verilog.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2026-03-26T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["DLCO", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/the-fall-of-my-freshman-year/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/the-fall-of-my-freshman-year/", "title": "The fall of my freshman year", "content_html": "<h1>The fall of my freshman year</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"../assets/covers/the-fall-of-my-freshman-year.jpeg\"></p>\n<p>\u4e00\u4e2a\u666e\u901a\u7684 Review\u3002\u4f1a\u6162\u6162\u66f4\u65b0\u3002</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/the-fall-of-my-freshman-year.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2026-01-17T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Review", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/the-storm-in-foundational-mathematics-konigs-paradox/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/the-storm-in-foundational-mathematics-konigs-paradox/", "title": "The Storm in Foundational Mathematics: Ko\u0308nig's Paradox", "content_html": "<h1>The Storm in Foundational Mathematics: Ko\u0308nig's Paradox</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Gyula Konig proposed the following paradox: By the Well Ordering Theorem, the real number set $\\mathbb{R}$ can be well ordered. We study the elements of $\\mathbb{R}$ and classify them. If a real number can be defined using a finite number of symbols, then we say it is finitely definable. Otherwise, we say it is undefinable. Obviously, undefinable real numbers exist, because finitely definable real numbers must be countable, while $\\mathbb{R}$ is uncountable. It is also obvious that, in the well order, the \"smallest\" elements, i.e., the beginning elements, are finitely definable. So the question is where we can find the first undefinable number. If $x$ is the first undefinable number, then its immediate predecessor is finitely definable. However, the above relationship with a finitely definable number should make $x$ finitely definable as well.</p>\n<p>How do you think of this paradox? Write an essay of no more than 1000 words.</p>\n</blockquote>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/the-storm-in-foundational-mathematics-konigs-paradox.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2025-11-20T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Math", "Studying"]}, {"id": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/welcome-to-my-new-blog/", "url": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/posts/welcome-to-my-new-blog/", "title": "Welcome to my new blog!", "content_html": "<h1>Welcome to my new blog!</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"../assets/covers/welcome-to-my-new-blog.jpg\"></p>\n<p>\u628a\u535a\u5ba2\u8fc1\u79fb\u5230 Material for Mkdocs \u4e0a\u5566</p>\n<p>\u5e94\u8be5\u4f1a\u770b\u8d77\u6765\u6b63\u7ecf\u4e00\u70b9\uff08\uff1f\u7136\u540e\u53ef\u80fd\u4f1a\u5c1d\u8bd5\u4e00\u4e9b\u81ea\u5b9a\u4e49\u7684 CSS\uff0c\u4e5f\u8bb8\u4f1a\u6bd4\u8f83\u597d\u770b\u5427\u3002</p>\n<p>!!! fail...</p>", "image": "https://blog.xmzheng.cn/assets/images/social/posts/welcome-to-my-new-blog.png", "date_modified": "2026-06-16T16:41:45+00:00", "date_published": "2025-12-26T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": ["Living"]}]}